Class FatalSessionException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable

        • com.ausregistry.jtoolkit2.session.FatalSessionException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class FatalSessionException
extends java.lang.Exception
    Thrown to indicate that attempts to configure and/or open a Session failed in such a way as to indicate that further attempts to open a session with the same configuration would also fail. The SessionProperties should be examined in conjunction with the cause of this exception and any associated log messages to identify the problem and resolve the issue.
